docs.abstract: Federal investigators say they have found huge gaps in the regulation of assisted living facilities that take care of Medicaid beneficiaries.
docs.snippet: Federal investigators say they have found huge gaps in the regulation of assisted living facilities that take care of Medicaid beneficiaries.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal investigators say they have found huge gaps in the regulation of assisted living facilities, a shortfall that they say has potentially jeopardized the care of hundreds of thousands of people served by the booming industry.

headline.main: U.S. Pays Billions for ‘Assisted Living,’ but What Does It Get?
headline.print_headline: Gaps Found in Scrutiny Of Assisted Living Homes

docs.abstract: The Trump administration said it would suspend a program that stabilizes markets by paying billions to insurers that enroll many unhealthy people under the Affordable Care Act.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration said it would suspend a program that stabilizes markets by paying billions to insurers that enroll many unhealthy people under the Affordable Care Act.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration said Saturday that it was suspending a program that pays billions of dollars to insurers to stabilize health insurance markets under the Affordable Care Act, a freeze that could increase uncertainty in the markets and drive up premiums this fall.

headline.main: Health Insurers Warn of Market Turmoil as Trump Suspends Billions in Payments
headline.print_headline: U.S. Warns It Is Halting Payments  To Insurers

docs.abstract: The Trump administration has announced that it is slashing grants to nonprofit organizations that help people get health insurance under the Affordable Care Act.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration has announced that it is slashing grants to nonprofit organizations that help people get health insurance under the Affordable Care Act.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration announced on Tuesday that it was slashing grants to nonprofit organizations that help people obtain health insurance under the Affordable Care Act, the latest step in an escalating attack on the law that threatens to destabilize its insurance markets.

headline.main: Trump Officials Slash Grants That Help Consumers Get Obamacare
headline.print_headline: Trump Officials Slash Grants That Help Consumers Get Obamacare

docs.abstract: The Trump administration has unveiled a Medicare program that closely resembles the Obama-era efforts to change the way doctors and hospitals are paid.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration has unveiled a Medicare program that closely resembles the Obama-era efforts to change the way doctors and hospitals are paid.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In a notable back flip, the Trump administration has decided that maybe the Obama administration was right in its efforts to change the way doctors and hospitals are paid under Medicare.

headline.main: Trump Officials, After Rejecting Obama Medicare Model, Adopt One Like It
headline.print_headline: Trump Officials Rejected An Obama Medicare Idea, But Now Adopt One Like It

docs.abstract: The administration is poised to issue a rule making it easier for small businesses to band together and create insurance plans that skirt many requirements of the Affordable Care Act.
docs.snippet: The administration is poised to issue a rule making it easier for small businesses to band together and create insurance plans that skirt many requirements of the Affordable Care Act.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration is poised to issue a sweeping rule that makes it easier for small businesses to band together to create health insurance plans that skirt many requirements of the Affordable Care Act, offering lower costs but also fewer benefits.

headline.main: Trump to Issue Rule That Weakens Affordable Care Act
headline.print_headline: Trump to Let Businesses Skirt Portions Of Health Act

docs.snippet: An independent federal study said the proposal could increase government spending by $1.2 billion next year, compared with the $96 million to $168 million a year estimated by the administration.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s plan to expand access to skimpy short-term health insurance policies, as an alternative to the Affordable Care Act, would affect more people and cost the government more money than the administration estimated, an independent federal study says.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration says it plans to roll back a rule issued by President Barack Obama that prevents doctors, hospitals and health insurance companies from discriminating against transgender people.

headline.print_headline: Trump Plan Could Curb Transgender People’s Access to Health Services

docs.abstract: Breaking a campaign promise, President Trump will not push for the plan, which was popular with voters but not other Republican politicians, when he speaks on Friday about soaring prescription costs.
docs.snippet: Breaking a campaign promise, President Trump will not push for the plan, which was popular with voters but not other Republican politicians, when he speaks on Friday about soaring prescription costs.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump will lay out on Friday a broad strategy to reduce prescription drug prices, but in a break from one of his most popular campaign promises, he will not call for Medicare to negotiate lower prices with drug manufacturers, senior administration officials said.

headline.main: Trump to Drop Call for Medicare to Negotiate Lower Drug Prices
headline.print_headline: President Has Proposal to Lower Drug Costs, but Not the Way He Promised

docs.abstract: Supporters of the “right to try” bill said it would give dying patients a chance to obtain potentially helpful prescription drugs without waiting for the completion of clinical trials.
docs.snippet: Supporters of the “right to try” bill said it would give dying patients a chance to obtain potentially helpful prescription drugs without waiting for the completion of clinical trials.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House, spurred on by President Trump, passed a bill on Wednesday that would give patients with terminal illnesses a right to try unproven experimental treatments.

headline.main: House Passes Bill That Would Give Patients Access to Experimental Drugs
headline.print_headline: House Passes Bill to Allow the Terminally Ill to Try Unproven Experimental Drugs

docs.abstract: Alex M. Azar II, President Trump’s nominee for health secretary, told senators that he was wary of proposals for Medicare to negotiate drug prices.
docs.snippet: Alex M. Azar II, President Trump’s nominee for health secretary, told senators that he was wary of proposals for Medicare to negotiate drug prices.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Alex M. Azar II, President Trump’s nominee for secretary of health and human services, said Tuesday that he was wary of proposals for the government to negotiate drug prices for Medicare beneficiaries, an idea endorsed by Mr. Trump in the 2016 campaign.

headline.main: Trump Likes Drug Price Negotiations; His Nominee for Health Secretary Doesn’t
headline.print_headline: Health Nominee Is Wary Of Negotiating Drug Prices
